The paper proposes a new interest point detector that is robust to noise and illumination changes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses an adaptive coding mechanism and measures blob significance, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results on standard datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
